
What does each line do?


#include <stdio.h>   // Standard input/output library, provides printf()

int main(void)       // Program entry point, returns an int value

printf("Hello, world!\n");  // Prints a string to standard output

return 0;            // Terminates the program successfully


 How to compile and run it on Linux
1 save the file
hello.c

2️⃣ Compile
gcc hello.c -o hello

3️⃣ Run
./hello


Output:

Hello, world! 


